args: *yaaawn* Good morning, Cleo.\nLooks like we're in for another scorcher.
Good morning, {player_name}.\nHeh... It's unlike you to have slept in so\nlate.
Have I? My apologies. I didn't realize the\ntime. Is everyone else already awake?
Well, at least I rose before HER. Ha ha.\nThough I'm still curious what she meant\nyesterday about rebelling against summer.
I heard about that. Very curious.
I have no idea what she's planning.\nShe went to bed last night saying her\nuprising ＂begins on the morrow.＂ *shrug*
Sleeping past noon makes for a poor\nopening salvo, I should think. I suppose\nI'll go check on her.
Oh, Mitsuhiiide? Time to rise and shi—
Hm? She's not in bed. Mitsuhide...?
Ouch. I just stubbed my toe on that...\nThat, uh...
Everyone... I... Th-there... In the storage\ncompartment under the flooring...
What is it? What's in... WAUGH?!
There's a person stuffed inside!\nAre those Mitsuhide's feet sticking out?!
Are you serious?! C'mon, Mitsuhide!\nWake up! Rrgh... Who did this to you?!
Could she have been targeted by an\nassassin? Some enemy of the Wyrmclan\nleaders?
Oh. Morning. ...What? Why do all of you\nlook like you saw a ghost?
For the love of everything holy...
Ugh, what's got you lot so cranky? I just\nwoke up. Stop screaming in my ear.
The heat had me tossing and turning all\nnight. I thought it might be cooler under\nthe floorboards, so I crawled in to find out.
Turns out I'm a GENIUS, because it's super\nnice down there! Almost chilly, even.

I mean, what a find! So, lovely as it is to
see you all, I've got a climate-controlled
burrow to get back to. Call me in a few
hours? Actually, don't. I'll call you.
Enough! My heart can't take any more!
Unbelievable. She actually crammed\nHERSELF down there.
Don't you need to wake up and start\nyour day by now, Mitsuhide?!
I very much beg to differ! And what of the\nrevolution?! Where has all your talk of\nstriking back at summer gone?
Hasn't gone anywhere. I'm in the heat of\nbattle right now.
This is what ＂battle＂ looks like to you?
Ugh... Let me put this in simpler terms\nfor you: summer hot. Me no like hot.
You're lovely people, but you really aren't\nthe sharpest. Look. It's hot. I aim to spend\nthe season as cool and inert as possible.
THAT is how you strike back at summer.
So, if you'll excuse me, I'm going to get\nback to my radical, revolutionary, chilly,\nlazy nap. Buh-bye, now.
Willful inertia as a radical act of defiance\nagainst the summer heat...
(How is that any different from what\nshe normally does?)
